Confguring logging

Jenkins logging can be configured through a properties file and
java.util.logging.config.file Java property. For example:

mkdir data
cat > data/log.properties <<EOF
handlers=java.util.logging.ConsoleHandler
jenkins.level=FINEST
java.util.logging.ConsoleHandler.level=FINEST
EOF
docker run --name myjenkins -p 8080:8080 -p 50000:50000  --env JAVA_OPTS="-Djava.util.logging.config.file=/var/jenkins_home/log.properties -Djava.awt.headless=true -Xmx12288m"  -v `pwd`/data:/var
